title: Finland Balance of Trade
description: Finland recorded a trade deficit of 330 EUR Million in September of 2022. Balance of Trade in Finland averaged 168.01 EUR Million from 1975 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 1749.60 EUR Million in November of 2002 and a record low of -1410 EUR Million in March of 2022. International trade makes a third of Finlandâ€™s GDP. Finnish principal exports are: telecommunications equipment, passenger cars and forestry products and paper and paperboard. Finnish principal imports are food stuffs, petroleum and petroleum products, chemicals, transport equipment, iron and steel, machinery, textile yarn and fabrics and grains. European Union makes 55 percent of the total trade. The largest trade flows are with Germany, Russia, Sweden, China and U.S. This page provides - Finland Balance of Trade - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
